        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 12 at 5:37PM EDT by NWS Columbia SC</headline>
        <description>At 537 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Mt Pisgah, or 21 miles northwest of Hartsville, moving north at 20
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts 40 to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pageland, Carolina Sandhills Wildlife Refuge, Mt Pisgah, Buford,
Mcbee, Jefferson, Ruby, Mount Croghan, Chesterfield Ruby Middle
School, High Point Fire Station, Tradesville, Middendorf, Bay Springs
Fire Station, Forty Acre Rock Preserve, Taxahaw, Kershaw Correctional
Institution, and Central High School.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
